<div id="review_3513819074" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3513819074" />
    <a title="Barbara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10357567-barbara"><img alt="Barbara" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1340209769p2/10357567.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3513819074?book_show_action=true">Aug 25, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Barbara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Barbara" href="/user/show/10357567-barbara">Barbara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780753823132" href="/book/show/9682371-the-frozen-heart">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3513819074" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7729558215015077280">&quot;One of the two Spains will freeze your heart&quot; -said Spanish poet Antonio Machado, who died in 1939 after experiencing the devastation of the Civil War. It is this Civil War which is the background and the ongoing underlying experience of this huge novel, which traces the fortunes of two families, on different sides of the divide. These families are linked, but we only discover this very gradually (which is probably why there are no family trees even though that would have been useful). The fina</span>
  <span id="freeText7729558215015077280" style="display:none">"One of the two Spains will freeze your heart" -said Spanish poet Antonio Machado, who died in 1939 after experiencing the devastation of the Civil War. It is this Civil War which is the background and the ongoing underlying experience of this huge novel, which traces the fortunes of two families, on different sides of the divide. These families are linked, but we only discover this very gradually (which is probably why there are no family trees even though that would have been useful). The final words of the novel emphasise that this story is just "one more story, one of many so similar" - stories of betrayal and memory, and identity, and what it means to live in fear. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7729558215015077280" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
