<span id="freeTextContainer7380091492520672114">Hate to give it one star but after forcing my way through it...well, I didn&apos;t feel as sunny as Spain and the rain clearly does fall all the time on the plain.<br/><br/>TOO. LONG. WAY. TOO. LONG. <br/><br/>How did anyone keep up with this?<br/><br/>The premise for the story is fantastico - past and present family saga with a cast of characters and some wrong-doing and parts of history we seldom read about. The parts in Madrid in the war are gripping.<br/><br/>But - there are so many characters and it hops and hops from one to another w</span>
  <span id="freeText7380091492520672114" style="display:none">Hate to give it one star but after forcing my way through it...well, I didn't feel as sunny as Spain and the rain clearly does fall all the time on the plain.<br /><br />TOO. LONG. WAY. TOO. LONG. <br /><br />How did anyone keep up with this?<br /><br />The premise for the story is fantastico - past and present family saga with a cast of characters and some wrong-doing and parts of history we seldom read about. The parts in Madrid in the war are gripping.<br /><br />But - there are so many characters and it hops and hops from one to another with a structure that Einstein couldn't fathom so you never really understand who is who. Then it hops from past to present so just as you are into the story and you think - yes, this is it - you go back to the present.<br /><br />And as for the interminable stuff on physics.<br /><br />Perhaps it works better in Spanish? That's all I can say.</span>
