  <span id="freeText14735780988826841834" style="display:none">Oh my ....<br />One of the best books I ever read... and I've read quite some...<br />It does take a bit to get into the story, as a foreign language reader, because it is very Spanish :-), very elaborate writing, not something we cold northern are used to. ( I am so going to be fined at the library...) But, if you can, you should totally read it in its original language and if not, please look for a copy in your language!<br /> I'm definitely reading more of Almudena Grandes after this one. Went through different stages of emotional uproar reading this book, I think I could say "outrage" is what stays behind. It makes me understand Spain better. <br />Total emotional rollercoaster. MUST READ!!!!!!<br /></span>
