    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2060943990" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2060943990" />
    <a title="Janet Panter" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/54725973-janet-panter"><img alt="Janet Panter" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1460132453p2/54725973.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2060943990?book_show_action=true">Feb 23, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Janet Panter" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Janet Panter" href="/user/show/54725973-janet-panter">Janet Panter</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/20371021-the-frozen-heart">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2060943990" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10520421238063256322">This is a LONG book, which I only really started to enjoy reading about half way in. It may be that the paperback version has a family tree on the first page - if it hasn&apos;t, then it certainly should have. The ebook version did not. Also, no chapters to speak of and it took me a while to get used to the sudden changes in narrator and era mid-page. And of course the fact that in Spanish families first names get passed down from generation to generation adds to the general confusion. This is a powe</span>
  <span id="freeText10520421238063256322" style="display:none">This is a LONG book, which I only really started to enjoy reading about half way in. It may be that the paperback version has a family tree on the first page - if it hasn't, then it certainly should have. The ebook version did not. Also, no chapters to speak of and it took me a while to get used to the sudden changes in narrator and era mid-page. And of course the fact that in Spanish families first names get passed down from generation to generation adds to the general confusion. This is a powerful story but not that easy to follow, even in translation! I kept wanting to look back to check details, which isn't that easy on on Kindle. I'm glad I stuck with it though.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10520421238063256322" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


