<div id="review_173490391" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/173490391" />
    <a title="Lynne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2357744-lynne"><img alt="Lynne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1395235216p2/2357744.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/173490391?book_show_action=true">Jun 03, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lynne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lynne" href="/user/show/2357744-lynne">Lynne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780753823132" href="/book/show/9682371-the-frozen-heart">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer173490391" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10284354880622174591">This was a long read being 780 pages. That is what attracted me to it initially.<br/>The premise of the story was good with historical facts about the country of Spain and <br/>the political parties, communists and some about WWII. The story revolved around the intertwining of two different families over 3 generations with it being told in first person of grandson at the present time. <br/>The thing that is always so disappointing to me is the sex and repeated use of the &quot;f&quot; word. It takes away from the story.</span>
  <span id="freeText10284354880622174591" style="display:none">This was a long read being 780 pages. That is what attracted me to it initially.<br />The premise of the story was good with historical facts about the country of Spain and <br />the political parties, communists and some about WWII. The story revolved around the intertwining of two different families over 3 generations with it being told in first person of grandson at the present time. <br />The thing that is always so disappointing to me is the sex and repeated use of the "f" word. It takes away from the story. I skipped over as much as possible to find out how the author ended this story because I did enjoy the story line.<br />I would like to read more of her works because of her abilitiy to write a great book but won't because of the sex and language.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10284354880622174591" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
